# SEQUENCE 10 — THE BOWL BEYOND ITS OWNER

/* TRACE: FU-056 | SC-037 */

EXT. KANCHI — FAMINE RELIEF CAMP — MORNING #66#

The Amudhasurabhi stands among ordinary people.

But the bowl is not the system.

People organise water.

Others cook.

Others record needs and carry food to those unable to reach the centre.

Compassion has become shared work.

/* TRACE: FU-057 | SC-038 */

INT. RELIEF HALL — DAY #67#

A worker asks Manimekalai who owns the vessel.

MANIMEKALAI
Wherever compassion exists, ownership must become unnecessary.

She gives principles, not orders.

The workers continue without waiting for her.

/* TRACE: FU-058 | SC-039 */

EXT. KANCHI — CITY EDGE — SUNSET #68#

Madhavi, Sudhamathi and Chitrapathi watch the city change.

They understand that Manimekalai's journey belongs to many lives, not one person.

/* TRACE: FU-059 | SC-040 */

INT. QUIET COURTYARD — NIGHT #69#

Manimekalai remembers those who brought her to compassion.

Udayakumaran.

Aputhiran.

Aadhirai.

The hungry.

The grieving.

Connection, not burden.

/* TRACE: FU-060 | SC-041 */

EXT. KANCHI — PUBLIC ROAD — DAWN #70#

The relief network continues.

The camera follows hands giving and receiving.

Not the miracle.

The people.

/* TRACE: FU-061 | SC-042 */

EXT. SEA HORIZON — MORNING #71#

Aputhiran's memory returns.

Not as a ghost.

As a question answered.

Compassion survived because it changed form.

/* TRACE: FU-062 | SC-043 */

EXT. KANCHI — FEEDING SPACE — DAY #72#

Manimekalai walks away from the centre.

No one follows because they depend on her.

They continue because they learned together.

The bowl remains.

The owner disappears.

The service continues.

FADE OUT.

END.